Example... I have hash, '123'. IPFS will node it all together, but not actually store that hash on your computer, just make it globally access able. But, if you 'pin' that hash, it will put it into that global node, making it more readily avail on the edge network for others to see in more remote areas to the initial seed computer.

If you are wanting to have your own IPFS, where you have QoS of your own stuff and not have to worry about some 'centralized' or '3rd party' My suggestion would be an AWS or Digital Ocean server. AWS will give you a bit more flexibility of your storage amounts and both are fairly inexpensive. If you want something that's not a 'centralized' business, I'd suggest looking into Flux. They are partnered with Meowcoin and might be a better solution.
